snippet.textDisplay: It amazes me the arrogance of journalists, that guy playing down Everton must be a kopite. Where was Man City in 1999? Third Tier of English football. Where was Chelsea in 1988? Second tier of English football. Both were mediocre clubs when Everton were winning league titles in the 80's. Everton have had absolutely no investment for 20 years, at a time when the Premie League went global. Prior the the EPL era, Everton had more league titles than Man Utd. It's not like Carlo Ancelotti is going to a Championship club. Man City is a perfect example of how times can change in football dramatically, in 2009 they were just out of fighting relegation, in 2012 they were champions of England. Now it's 2019, journalists like to pretend that they and Chelsea were always on top. Which is far from true.

If you aim low you get nowhere. Maybe we can't compete with the more successful clubs but we should at least try. Or we might as well not bother.

What a fantastic day this is.
